# Commit Message Template
#
# FOR SMALL CHANGES (use single line):
# Brief description of what changed
#
# FOR LARGER CHANGES (use this format):
# Brief summary header (imperative mood, no period)
#
# - First change made
# - Second change made
# - Third change made
#
# Type: <type>
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Types:
#   feat      - New feature
#   fix       - Bug fix
#   refactor  - Code refactoring (no functionality change)
#   change    - Behavior/functionality change
#   docs      - Documentation only
#   style     - Formatting, whitespace, etc.
#   test      - Adding or updating tests
#   chore     - Maintenance, dependencies, tooling
#   perf      - Performance improvement
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Examples:
#
# Small change:
#   Fix typo in login validation message
#
# Large change:
#   Refactor authentication system
#
#   - Migrate from JWT to session-based auth
#   - Update user model with session fields
#   - Add middleware for session management
#   - Update tests for new auth flow
#
#   Type: refactor
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Tips:
# - Use imperative mood ("Add feature" not "Added feature")
# - Keep header under 72 characters
# - Be specific about what changed and why
# - Reference issue numbers when applicable
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────